@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Main"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

MostDownloaded is a small statistics generator for the
filecatalogue.  I have been programming on it now and then.
I thought I'd release it for others to enjoy it.

@endnode

@node "Distribution" "Distribution"
@next "Responsibility"
@prev "Introduction"
@{b}Distribution@{ub}

This version of MostDownloaded is freely distributable for
non-commercial use.

You can spread this complete archive via AmiNet, ADS, SAN and
other non-profit networks and BBS:es.

@endnode

@node "Responsibility" "Responsibility"
@next "Compatibility"
@prev "Distribution"
@{b}Responsibility@{ub}

The author of MostDownloaded will not take any responsibilities
for any loss/damage of data or otherwise important information,
hardware problems or your users staking out your home and
following you where ever you go.


With other words - @{b}Don't blame me!@{ub}
@endnode

@node "Compatibility" "Compatibility"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Responsibility"
@{b}Compatibility@{ub}

MostDownloaded has a big possibility to work on earlier versions
than Xenolink 1.90+, the code for scanning filesections hasn't
changed that much.

MostDownloaded has so far been tested on the following computer
setups;

@{i}Amiga 1200@{ui}  68030/50MHz, 6 MB RAM, Kickstart 3.0/39.106,
            Workbench 3.0/39.29, Xenolink 1.95.
            Owned by author @{"Tommy Green" link "Author Info" 0}

@{i}Amiga 500@{ui}   68000/8MHz, 9 MB RAM, Kickstart 2.04/37.175,
            Workbench 2.1/38.28, Xenolink 1.90.
            Owned by author @{"Tommy Green" link "Author Info" 0}
@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "Documentation"
@prev "Compatibility"
@{b}Requirements@{ub}

MostDownloaded requires at least,

                                  AmigaDOS 2.04/V37
                                  approx. 4096 bytes stack
                                  Xenolink 1.90+, earlier versions
                                  could work also, see @{"compatibility" link "Compatibility" 0}
@endnode

@node "Documentation" "Documentation"
@next "Author Info"
@prev "Requirements"
@{b}Documentation@{ub}

MostDownloaded has no usage, you just run it.

@{i}Example@{ui}

If you enter this string in Shell/CLI:

MostDownloaded

the output might look like this in the Shell/CLI:

MostDownloaded 37.15, copyright ©1994,1995 by Tommy Green

               Top 20 list of most downloaded files

Dls FileName             Filesection                    Uploader
--- -------------------- ------------------------------ -----------------------
 46 LZX100.LHA           Archivers                      XAreaFix 1.0
 and so on..


@endnode

@node "Author Info" "Author Info"
@next "Acknowledgments"
@prev "Documentation"
@{b}Author information@{ub}

I'm 22 years old, born just south of Stockholm, Sweden in 1972.

I became interested in computers when my parents bought me a
Philips G7000 in the mid-80s.  8-)

Later I bought a C-128, a couple of years later I laid my hands on
my first Amiga, an Amiga 500 with Kickstart 1.3 (I still got it at
home, it served as BBS-computer until October 1994).

Did my military service from July 1993 to June 1994, in the
Swedish Air Force.

As mentioned I replaced my BBS-computer later on, with a A1200 and
a Blizzard A1230-II/50MHz card with four megabytes.

Right now I'm cooping with unemployment with 500,000 other people
here in Sweden.

I can be reached for bugreports and suggestions in XENOLINK_UTIL
as well as a netmail to 2:201/344.0.  
@endnode

